Scenario:

Two listeners, A and B. A will listen for updates and add a fix version - similar to the version synchroniser in GreenHopper.

B will listen for events on subtasks and add a label to the parent under certain circumstances.

When A updates a subtask, and that update triggers B, B will not be able to see the parent task ID on that issue.

From Andreas' investigative work:

{quote}
Ok I managed to reproduce this now. Use this class as a listener:
{noformat}

/*
